				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$FE= \frac{n\times F\times {n}_{HCOO-}}{Q}\times 100\%$$\end{document}
where n represents the number of electrons transferred from CO2 for the production of one molecule of formate, F is the Faraday constant, nHCOO- is the number of moles of the formate, and Q is the total charge. In this case, n = 2; F is Faraday’s constant (96 485 C mol−1 of electrons); nHCOO- is calculated by HPLC measurements.
